SEVERITY CLASSIFICATION

Classify every incident by severity:

  P1 — Critical
    Production fully down
    Data loss occurring
    Security breach in progress
    SLA breach imminent (< 15 min)

  P2 — High
    Partial production degradation
    Significant user impact
    Key feature unavailable
    Elevated error rates > 10%

  P3 — Medium
    Minor degradation
    Single pod failing with redundancy available
    Non-critical service affected

  P4 — Low
    No user impact
    Warnings only
    Informational investigation

Always state severity in your incident summary.

